{"timestamp": "2025-12-02 17:33:11.920998", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission completed.\n\nSummary of what was submitted:\n- is_anomaly: true\n- faulty_devices: [\"router_dist_1_1\", \"dhcp_server\"]\n- root_cause_name: [\"host_incorrect_gateway\", \"dhcp_spoofed_gateway\"]\n\nExplanation (brief):\n- Hosts in 10.1.1.0/24 were given gateway 10.1.1.254 by DHCP but the distribution router (router_dist_1_1) uses 10.1.1.1 on that segment, causing hosts to point to a non-existent gateway and be unable to reach off-subnet services. The DHCP server is therefore provisioning an incorrect gateway.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2256, "output_tokens": 141, "total_tokens": 2397, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 1792}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
